WEBVTT

00:15.600 --> 00:18.467
IT IS MY FAULT
HECTOR IS DEAD.

00:18.686 --> 00:21.428
I AM THE ONE WHO ASKED HIM
TO HELP WITH MILLER BECK.

00:21.647 --> 00:25.435
HECTOR'S DEAD
BECAUSE DAVID RIDGES KILLED HIM.

00:31.032 --> 00:32.818
SO NIGHTHORSE LIED?

00:32.992 --> 00:35.608
DAVID IS ALIVE?

00:35.786 --> 00:39.153
I THINK NIGHTHORSE SENT
HIS FORMER EMPLOYEE

00:39.332 --> 00:41.414
TO KILL THE ONLY MAN
WHO COULD PROVE YOU'RE INNOCENT.

00:41.584 --> 00:43.666
BRANCH AND I TRIED
TO TALK TO HIM,

00:43.836 --> 00:45.747
BUT WE DIDN'T GET
VERY FAR.

00:45.922 --> 00:48.334
TURNS OUT
HE'S HIRED MALACHI STRAND

00:48.508 --> 00:49.964
AS A NEW HEAD OF SECURITY.

00:50.134 --> 00:51.089
FUNNY.

00:51.844 --> 00:53.084
MALACHI DID NOT MENTION THAT

00:53.262 --> 00:56.800
WHEN HE CAME IN YESTERDAY
AND OFFERED TO BUY MY BAR.

00:56.974 --> 00:58.510
[SIGHS]

00:58.726 --> 01:00.967
THIS WHOLE THING'S STARTING
TO FEEL LIKE A CONSPIRACY.

01:02.688 --> 01:04.349
I JUST NEED
TO FIND A WAY

01:04.565 --> 01:06.647
TO GET AT MALACHI
AND NIGHTHORSE.

01:06.859 --> 01:08.770
FIGURE OUT
WHAT THEY HAVE PLANNED.

01:08.945 --> 01:11.402
I KNOW OF ONE GUY
WHO IS WORKING FOR MALACHI.

01:11.572 --> 01:15.360
WHEN MALACHI WAS IN PRISON,
THE MAN WAS...

01:15.535 --> 01:19.448
STAKING OUT MY BAR,
SAVING MALACHI'S SEAT.

01:19.622 --> 01:22.159
THIS MAN TELL YOU
HIS NAME?

01:25.586 --> 01:27.622
HE COMES BACK,
YOU CALL ME.

01:27.797 --> 01:28.877
WE'LL TRACK HIM DOWN.

01:29.048 --> 01:30.754
[SIGHS]

01:33.219 --> 01:35.631
YOU MEAN
YOU WILL TRACK HIM DOWN.

01:49.360 --> 01:51.521
[ENGINE SHUTS OFF]

02:02.498 --> 02:04.659
ROUGH NIGHT?

02:04.834 --> 02:07.291
I GOT YOU COFFEE AND A DANISH
IF YOU CAN STOMACH IT.

02:09.505 --> 02:10.915
COME ON, BUDDY.
WAKE UP.

02:11.090 --> 02:12.591
WAKE UP.

02:22.893 --> 02:24.474
HE'S OKAY.

02:25.855 --> 02:28.016
HE'S ALL RIGHT.
A FEW TOO MANY.

02:28.190 --> 02:29.350
[CHUCKLES]

02:46.959 --> 02:47.869
FERG!

02:48.836 --> 02:49.586
FERG!

02:49.754 --> 02:51.745
WHAT'S GOING ON,
SHERIFF?
NOTHING.

02:51.922 --> 02:53.662
I JUST NEED YOUR HELP
TO GET THIS DRUNK GUY

02:53.841 --> 02:55.547
BACK TO THE STATION
WITHOUT MAKING A SCENE.

02:55.718 --> 02:57.208
LET'S PICK HIM UP.

02:57.887 --> 02:59.343
O KAY.

02:59.513 --> 03:01.595
UH, HE'S NOT DRUNK.

03:02.224 --> 03:03.600
OF COURSE HE'S DRUNK.

03:03.934 --> 03:05.435
GET HIM BACK ACROSS THE STREET.
OKAY.

03:05.645 --> 03:06.805
ONE, TWO, THREE.

03:07.021 --> 03:07.885
[GRUNTS]

03:08.397 --> 03:09.773
WE CAN'T WALK HIM.

03:09.982 --> 03:11.438
THIS GUY'S DEAD.

03:11.651 --> 03:12.515
[GRUNTS]

03:13.069 --> 03:15.025
JUST KEEP IT TOGETHER,
FERG.

03:15.988 --> 03:16.943
UP.

03:18.240 --> 03:19.366
COME ON.

03:20.076 --> 03:21.316
COME ON, FERG.

03:22.870 --> 03:24.451
EXCUSE US, LADIES.

03:24.622 --> 03:26.032
I GOT ALL THE WEIGHT.

03:26.207 --> 03:27.037
PICK HIM UP.

03:27.208 --> 03:28.368
LIFT HIM UP, FERG.

03:28.542 --> 03:30.203
MORNING. MORNING.
[CHUCKLES]

03:30.378 --> 03:32.869
[GRUNTS]

03:33.047 --> 03:34.082
[PANTING]

03:34.256 --> 03:36.713
SHERIFF,
WHY ARE WE DOING THIS?

03:36.884 --> 03:38.124
[PANTING]

03:40.012 --> 03:43.880
BECAUSE THIS DEAD MAN IS WORTH
$100 MILLION.

03:44.058 --> 03:44.968
[ EXHALES SHARPLY]

03:45.142 --> 03:47.929
UH, T-THIS BUM?
ARE YOU SERIOUS?

03:48.854 --> 03:51.937
ACCORDING TO HIS I.D.,
THIS IS WELLES VANBLARCOM.

03:52.149 --> 03:54.060
AS IN VANBLARCOM MINING?

03:55.528 --> 03:57.143
DIDN'T HIS MOM DIE
LIKE EIGHT YEARS AGO

03:57.321 --> 03:59.027
AND LEAVE HIM A BUNCH OF CASH
IN HER WILL?

03:59.198 --> 04:00.699
YEP.

04:00.866 --> 04:02.572
HE'S BEEN MISSING
FOR 30 YEARS.

04:03.327 --> 04:05.067
MOST PEOPLE FIGURED
HE WAS DEAD, SO...

04:05.371 --> 04:06.656
WHICH...

04:07.832 --> 04:08.696
HE IS.

04:08.999 --> 04:10.284
MY GOD,
I READ ALL ABOUT THIS.

04:10.459 --> 04:12.541
IT WAS ALL OVER THE NEWS,
EVEN IN PHILLY.

04:12.712 --> 04:15.749
WHICH IS WHY NONE OF YOU CAN SAY
A WORD ABOUT THIS.

04:15.923 --> 04:18.039
THIS IS NATIONAL NEWS.

04:18.217 --> 04:22.802
WE NEED TO NOTIFY
THE VANBLARCOMS AND MAKE AN I.D.

04:22.972 --> 04:24.883
BEFORE THE PRESS GETS
ANY WIND OF IT.

04:25.349 --> 04:26.555
ARE WE GONNA BRING THE FAMILY
INTO THE STATION?

04:26.726 --> 04:29.513
NO, IF THEY SHOW UP HERE
OR AT THE HOSPITAL,

04:29.729 --> 04:31.265
PEOPLE WILL START
ASKING QUESTIONS.

04:31.480 --> 04:32.811
NO.

04:33.023 --> 04:34.979
WE TAKE THE BODY TO THEM.

04:36.402 --> 04:38.939
SO...

04:39.113 --> 04:42.401
WE'RE CARRYING HIM
BACK DOWN THE STAIRS?

04:43.743 --> 04:45.153
[GLASS CLINKING]

04:48.372 --> 04:50.533
TABLE FOR ONE,
OR WILL MALACHI BE JOINING YOU?

04:51.208 --> 04:52.744
MALACHI WANTS HIS HEADS.

04:56.213 --> 04:57.714
I'M AFRAID
THAT WILL TAKE SOME TIME.

04:57.923 --> 04:59.038
THEY'RE ATTACHED
WITH HEX BOLTS.

04:59.300 --> 05:01.006
I NEED A SPECIAL WRENCH
TO TAKE THEM DOWN.

05:01.177 --> 05:02.713
COME BACK AT 5:00.

05:02.887 --> 05:04.343
I'LL BE HERE AT 2:00.

05:04.513 --> 05:06.049
HAVE THEM READY TO GO.

05:06.849 --> 05:08.510
[ FOOTSTEPS DEPART]

05:09.643 --> 05:11.929
SO, IT LOOKS LIKE
WELLES VANBLARCOM DIDN'T HAVE

05:12.146 --> 05:13.386
MUCH FAMILY.

05:13.564 --> 05:15.600
JUST A BROTHER, A SISTER,
AND A NEPHEW.

05:15.816 --> 05:19.434
THEIR COMBINED NET WORTH WAS
$500 MILLION.

05:20.029 --> 05:22.566
HOW DOES ONE FAMILY EVEN GET
THAT MUCH MONEY?

05:22.740 --> 05:24.150
SILVER.

05:24.325 --> 05:26.862
GRANDFATHER WAS A MINER
WHO STRUCK IT RICH.

05:28.370 --> 05:31.362
FAMILY'S PRACTICALLY
WYOMING ROYALTY.

05:32.708 --> 05:34.699
THAT WOULD EXPLAIN
THE CASTLE.

05:35.753 --> 05:37.084
[P.A. DINGS]

05:38.088 --> 05:39.077
MAN: CAN I HELP YOU?

05:39.298 --> 05:40.413
SHERIFF LONGMIRE.

05:40.591 --> 05:42.923
I'M HERE TO SEE
PENNY AND GRAHAM VANBLARCOM.

05:43.093 --> 05:44.879
[GATE BUZZES]

05:50.601 --> 05:51.966
HELLO, PENNY.

05:52.561 --> 05:53.550
HELLO, WALT.

05:53.813 --> 05:55.724
GRAHAM.
WALT.

05:55.940 --> 05:58.022
HI.

05:59.568 --> 06:01.149
THIS IS
DEPUTY MORETTI.

06:01.320 --> 06:02.275
PENNY: HELLO.

06:02.446 --> 06:03.652
I'M SORRY
ABOUT ALL THIS.

06:03.823 --> 06:05.313
ARE YOU SURE
IT'S HIM?

06:05.950 --> 06:09.283
WELL, WE FOUND AN I.D.
AND HIS SOCIAL SECURITY CARD.

06:09.453 --> 06:11.614
BOTH MATCH
YOUR BROTHER'S.

06:13.833 --> 06:15.994
WE NEED YOU TO IDENTIFY HIM
BEFORE IT'S OFFICIAL.

06:16.001 --> 06:17.787
I DON'T KNOW
HOW MUCH HELP WE'LL BE.

06:18.212 --> 06:19.918
WE WERE BOTH SO YOUNG
WHEN WELLES RAN AWAY.

06:26.095 --> 06:27.426
OH, MY GOD.

06:28.097 --> 06:31.305
I-I SUPPOSE IT'S HIM.

06:31.475 --> 06:33.306
HE LOOKS AN AWFUL LOT LIKE
THE SKETCH.

06:34.103 --> 06:34.808
YEAH.

06:35.437 --> 06:36.222
WHAT SKETCH?

06:36.438 --> 06:38.178
EIGHT YEARS AGO,
WHEN OUR MOTHER DIED

06:38.399 --> 06:42.108
AND LEFT WELLES' INHERITANCE,
WE HAD THIS SKETCH MADE.

06:42.278 --> 06:44.769
GRAHAM:
IT'S A PROJECTION OF WHAT WELLES
WOULD'VE LOOKED LIKE

06:44.947 --> 06:46.778
30 YEARS
AFTER THIS PICTURE WAS TAKEN.

06:46.991 --> 06:48.071
PENNY:
WE GAVE COPIES OF THE SKETCH

06:48.242 --> 06:49.948
TO DIFFERENT P.I.S
ALL ACROSS THE COUNTRY,

06:50.119 --> 06:51.825
EVEN OFFERED
A HUGE CASH REWARD,

06:52.079 --> 06:55.071
BUT, UH, THEY NEVER SHOWED UP
WITH ANYTHING.

06:55.249 --> 06:57.991
IT'S FUNNY HOW HE WAS MISSING
ALL THESE YEARS

06:58.168 --> 06:59.248
ONLY TO BE FOUND DEAD

06:59.420 --> 07:00.910
A FEW MILES
FROM HIS CHILDHOOD HOME.

07:01.088 --> 07:04.546
MAYBE HE WAS TRYING
TO COME HOME FINALLY.

07:04.717 --> 07:06.332
WISH HE WOULD'VE COME BACK
A LOT SOONER.

07:06.510 --> 07:07.920
WOULD'VE MEANT A LOT
TO OUR MOTHER.

07:08.095 --> 07:09.960
SHE NEVER STOPPED HOPING
THAT HE'D COME BACK.

07:10.139 --> 07:12.300
SHE EVEN SET A PLACE FOR HIM
FOR DINNER EVERY NIGHT.

07:12.474 --> 07:13.680
[BIRD SQUAWKS]
[GASPS]

07:13.851 --> 07:15.432
[SQUAWKS]
GEEZ!

07:15.644 --> 07:17.635
WHAT IS WITH
ALL THE BIRDS?!

07:17.855 --> 07:19.561
PENNY: MOM LOVED THEM.

07:19.773 --> 07:21.513
SHE EVEN LEFT MONEY IN HER WILL
TO MAINTAIN THEM.

07:21.734 --> 07:22.894
SHE LEFT
ALL SORTS OF PROVISIONS

07:23.068 --> 07:24.319
FOR US TO KEEP THIS PLACE
LIKE A SHRINE,

07:24.486 --> 07:27.193
BUT THE BIRDS,
THEY WERE HER PETS.

07:27.448 --> 07:28.528
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

07:28.699 --> 07:30.815
I KNOW SHE WOULD WANT WELLES'
BODY BURIED IN THE FAMILY PLOT.

07:31.076 --> 07:34.159
WOULD YOU MIND TAKING HIS BODY
TO THE -- TO THE MORTUARY?

07:34.330 --> 07:35.615
UNFORTUNATELY, UH...

07:35.831 --> 07:36.616
GRAHAM: WHO IS THIS?

07:36.790 --> 07:38.371
...WHEN A BODY'S FOUND
ON PUBLIC LAND,

07:38.542 --> 07:40.123
WE'RE REQUIRED
TO DO AN AUTOPSY.

07:40.294 --> 07:42.285
I PROMISE
TO KEEP THE MATTER PRIVATE.

07:42.463 --> 07:44.624
THANK YOU.
HOW DID YOU GET
THIS NUMBER?

07:46.842 --> 07:50.710
IT'S A REPORTER ASKING ABOUT
OUR BROTHER'S DEATH.

07:51.889 --> 07:53.425
HOW'D THEY FIND OUT?

07:53.933 --> 07:55.173
I TWEETED IT.

07:59.772 --> 08:02.184
STANDING BEAR!
IT'S 2:00.

08:02.399 --> 08:03.855
I'M A LITTLE BUSY.

08:04.068 --> 08:06.730
THE BAR SINK IS BROKEN.
THE HEADS ARE ON THE TABLE.

08:07.237 --> 08:09.319
YOU SURE
THIS IS EVERYTHING?

08:09.490 --> 08:11.151
I DON'T WANT
TO HAVE TO COME BACK.

08:11.325 --> 08:12.610
A SENTIMENT
WE BOTH SHARE.

08:20.501 --> 08:22.116
[INHALES SHARPLY]

08:22.294 --> 08:24.080
[GRUNTS]

08:29.468 --> 08:30.833
[GRUNTS]

08:43.232 --> 08:44.597
YOU KNOW,
I NEVER THOUGHT OF YOU

08:44.775 --> 08:45.981
AS THE GARDEN
PARTY TYPE,

08:46.151 --> 08:47.186
BUT YOU SEEMED
REAL COMFORTABLE

08:47.361 --> 08:48.646
WITH THE MONOPOLY TWINS
BACK THERE,

08:48.821 --> 08:49.936
ESPECIALLY PENNY.

08:50.114 --> 08:52.480
MY DAD LOOKED AFTER
THEIR STABLES.

08:52.658 --> 08:54.569
I'D GO IN SOMETIMES.

08:54.743 --> 08:56.324
PENNY WOULD COME DOWN
TO SKETCH THE HORSES

08:56.495 --> 08:57.325
WHILE WE WORKED.

08:57.496 --> 08:59.361
SKETCH THE HORSES?

08:59.540 --> 09:01.781
[CHUCKLING ] SOUNDS LIKE
SHE HAD A CRUSH ON YOU.

09:01.959 --> 09:02.823
[LAUGHS]

09:03.002 --> 09:04.492
WHAT WERE YOU LIKE
AT 12?

09:04.670 --> 09:06.035
CHATTY, I BET, RIGHT?

09:06.213 --> 09:07.498
[CHUCKLES]

09:12.261 --> 09:14.172
SHERIFF, HOW LONG AGO
DID THE VANBLARCOM HEIR DIE?

09:14.388 --> 09:15.969
HAD HE BEEN IN WYOMING
THIS WHOLE TIME, SHERIFF?

09:16.181 --> 09:18.342
SHERIFF, ARE YOU GETTING ANY
SORT OF REWARD FROM THE FAMILY?

09:18.559 --> 09:19.890
NO COMMENT.

09:21.145 --> 09:23.352
FERG: NOTHING. I GOT NOTHING.
IF YOU HIT CONFERENCE CALL --

09:23.564 --> 09:25.270
WE TRIED CALLING VIC
TO WARN YOU.

09:25.482 --> 09:26.983
OH,
THE PHONES GOT OVERLOADED.

09:27.192 --> 09:28.307
CALLS FROM THE REPORTERS,

09:28.485 --> 09:30.737
AND NOW THE WHOLE SYSTEM HAS
SHUT DOWN.

09:30.904 --> 09:32.815
FERG,
KEEP AN EYE ON THE DOOR.

09:34.575 --> 09:37.066
BRANCH:
SO, THE MISSING VANBLARCOM HEIR
FINALLY SHOWED UP?

09:37.244 --> 09:38.359
WHERE YOU BEEN?

09:38.537 --> 09:39.993
WORKING.

09:40.164 --> 09:43.622
GOT THAT TRANSCRIPT
FROM MALACHI'S PAROLE HEARING.

09:43.792 --> 09:44.907
ALSO TALKED WITH MY FRIEND

09:45.085 --> 09:46.541
WHO WORKS
WITH THE COUNTY ASSAYER.

09:46.712 --> 09:49.078
HE'S GOT MAPS OF ALL THE CAVES
NEAR WHERE WE FOUND HECTOR.

09:49.256 --> 09:51.588
I FIGURED WE'D PICK HIM UP,
HEAD OVER TO THE CAVES,

09:52.176 --> 09:53.256
START LOOKING
FOR RIDGES.

09:54.261 --> 09:55.922
[SIGHS]
I GOT MY HANDS FULL HERE.

09:56.555 --> 09:57.305
YOU GO.

09:57.473 --> 09:59.714
AS SOON AS THINGS DIE DOWN,
I'LL JOIN YOU.

09:59.892 --> 10:01.302
HEY, YOU KNOW,
I CAN GO WITH BRANCH

10:01.518 --> 10:02.303
TILL YOU CAN CATCH UP.

10:02.519 --> 10:03.804
I'M FINE ON MY OWN.

10:04.021 --> 10:05.181
WALT: TAKE HER.

10:06.857 --> 10:07.482
[DOOR OPENS]

10:07.691 --> 10:09.192
[SIGHS]

10:15.074 --> 10:16.655
HENRY.

10:23.749 --> 10:25.705
[RINGING]

10:25.876 --> 10:27.116
HENRY:
"IT IS A BEAUTIFUL DAY

10:27.294 --> 10:28.625
AT THE RED PONY
AND CONTINUAL SOIREE.

10:28.796 --> 10:29.876
NO ONE IS ABLE
TO COME TO THE PHONE,

10:30.047 --> 10:30.911
SO PLEASE LEAVE A MESSAGE. "

10:31.090 --> 10:32.375
[BEEP]

10:32.549 --> 10:34.130
NOT MUCH OF A SOIREE, HENRY.
I'M OUTSIDE.

10:34.885 --> 10:36.091
THE DOOR IS LOCKED,
AND WE HAD A MEETING,

10:36.261 --> 10:38.673
SO CALL ME, PLEASE.

10:51.527 --> 10:53.609
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

11:04.832 --> 11:05.821
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING]

11:10.712 --> 11:12.794
[BANGING]

11:13.966 --> 11:15.081
[GRUNTS]

11:16.927 --> 11:18.508
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

11:22.766 --> 11:23.881
[GRUNTING]

11:46.999 --> 11:48.159
SHIT.

11:49.168 --> 11:50.658
RUBY.
RUBY: HMM?

11:50.836 --> 11:52.701
FERG AND I ARE HEADING
TO DURANT MEMORIAL.

11:52.880 --> 11:55.371
THE AUTOPSY SHOWS THAT WELLES
DIED OF A DRUG OVERDOSE.

11:55.549 --> 11:56.755
SEEMS LIKE YOU'VE GOT

11:56.925 --> 11:58.586
QUITE THE CROWD OUT THERE,
LONGFINGER.

11:59.303 --> 12:01.168
YOU CAME BY EARLY
TO TALK.

12:01.346 --> 12:03.177
WE'RE READY TO TALK.

12:05.017 --> 12:08.225
WE FOUND THESE CAMERAS
THIS AFTERNOON THAT WERE HIDDEN

12:08.437 --> 12:11.270
OUTSIDE MY OFFICE
AND AT THE CONSTRUCTION SITE.

12:11.481 --> 12:13.642
WE THOUGHT
YOU MIGHT LIKE THEM BACK.

12:13.859 --> 12:16.521
WHAT MAKES YOU THINK
THEY BELONG TO ME?

12:16.695 --> 12:18.481
WELL, SEEMS YOU'VE TAKEN
A KEEN INTEREST

12:18.655 --> 12:20.691
IN, UH,
MR. NIGHTHORSE'S ACTIVITIES.

12:21.283 --> 12:22.944
SEE, I HAVE A HABIT
OF GETTING A WARRANT

12:23.285 --> 12:25.367
BEFORE I PLANT ANY
SURVEILLANCE EQUIPMENT, SO...

12:25.829 --> 12:29.037
THERE'S ONLY ONE STORE IN TOWN
THAT SELLS THESE CAMERAS.

12:29.208 --> 12:32.575
LAST WEEK, A MAN CAME IN
AND BOUGHT A WHOLE BUNCH.

12:32.753 --> 12:37.292
NAME ON THE RECEIPT WAS,
UH...

12:37.466 --> 12:39.252
BRANCH CON NALLY.

12:40.385 --> 12:42.671
I'M GONNA NEED
TO TALK TO YOUR DEPUTY.

12:45.182 --> 12:46.388
HE'S BUSY.

12:46.600 --> 12:48.136
UH-HUH.

12:52.856 --> 12:54.141
[DOOR OPENS]

12:54.358 --> 12:55.814
YOU MIGHT WANT
TO REEVALUATE

12:56.026 --> 12:57.812
SOME OF YOUR EMPLOYEES,
WALT.

12:59.321 --> 13:01.437
YOU'RE ONLY AS GOOD
AS THE PEOPLE YOU HIRE.

13:01.615 --> 13:02.900
[CHUCKLES]

13:04.243 --> 13:05.528
[DOOR CLOSES]

13:06.286 --> 13:07.571
FERG.

13:07.746 --> 13:09.737
GET BRANCH
ON YOUR CELLPHONE.

13:09.915 --> 13:10.745
NOW!
[DOOR OPENS]

13:10.916 --> 13:11.951
RUBY: HEY. PLEASE.

13:12.125 --> 13:13.626
I TOLD YOU ALL TO WAIT
IN THE FOYER.

13:13.794 --> 13:15.000
YOU HAVEN'T TOLD ME
ANYTHING.

13:15.170 --> 13:16.501
WHO ARE YOU?

13:16.672 --> 13:18.412
WELLES VANBLARCOM,

13:18.590 --> 13:21.332
AND REPORTS OF MY DEATH ARE
GREATLY EXAGGERATED.

13:29.017 --> 13:31.633
WALT:
I'LL ADMIT YOU LOOK SOMEWHAT
LIKE THIS POLICE SKETCH,

13:31.853 --> 13:34.185
BUT IF I'M GONNA BELIEVE
YOU'RE WELLES,

13:34.398 --> 13:35.604
I'LL NEED TO SEE
SOME PROOF.

13:35.816 --> 13:37.306
MY WORD'S NOT GOOD ENOUGH
FOR YOU?

13:38.068 --> 13:40.354
NOT WHEN THE MAN WE FOUND HAD
TWO FORMS OF I.D. SAYING

13:40.529 --> 13:42.190
HE WAS WELLES VANBLARCOM,
NO.

13:42.364 --> 13:43.479
I GAVE THOSE TO HIM.

13:43.657 --> 13:45.193
I GOT SICK
OF PEOPLE TRYING TO FIND ME.

13:45.367 --> 13:46.698
I DON'T EVEN GO BY WELLES
ANYMORE.

13:46.868 --> 13:48.529
EVERYONE JUST CALLS ME
JOHN.

13:49.162 --> 13:49.947
JOHN.

13:50.163 --> 13:51.289
WERE YOU AND THE DEAD MAN
CLOSE?

13:52.040 --> 13:54.372
I JUST MET HIM AT A BAR
ONE NIGHT IN CLEVELAND.

13:54.543 --> 13:55.658
HE LOOKED A LITTLE LIKE ME.

13:55.836 --> 13:57.292
ITHOUGHT,
"IF I GIVE HIM MY I.D.,

13:57.462 --> 13:58.747
I COULD DISAPPEAR
FOR GOOD."

13:59.172 --> 14:01.128
HOW DO I KNOW
YOU'RE NOT JUST SOME IMPOSTER

14:01.300 --> 14:03.507
TRYING TO LAY CLAIM
TO THE VANBLARCOM INHERITANCE?

14:03.677 --> 14:05.383
BECAUSE I DON'T WANT ANYTHING
FROM THEM.

14:05.554 --> 14:07.795
MONEY MESSES PEOPLE UP.

14:09.057 --> 14:11.764
I JUST CAME HERE BECAUSE I WANT
THAT MAN'S REAL FAMILY

14:11.977 --> 14:12.807
TO KNOW HE'S DEAD.

14:13.020 --> 14:14.135
CAN YOU GIVE ME HIS NAME?

14:14.354 --> 14:15.969
NO.
BUT YOU'RE A COP.

14:16.189 --> 14:17.474
I'M SURE YOU HAVE WAYS
OF FIGURING IT OUT.

14:17.691 --> 14:18.476
I DO.

14:18.692 --> 14:20.273
BUT BEFORE I START
LOOKING INTO IT,

14:20.444 --> 14:22.309
I NEED TO BE SURE
THAT YOU ARE WHO YOU SAY.

14:22.487 --> 14:24.603
NOW, THE FASTEST WAY
TO PROVE YOU'RE WELLES IS

14:24.781 --> 14:25.861
TO DO A DNA TEST.

14:26.033 --> 14:27.443
NOT A CHANCE.

14:27.617 --> 14:29.608
I'VE SPENT DECADES
TRYING TO KEEP MYSELF HIDDEN.

14:29.786 --> 14:32.402
I TAKE A DNA TEST,
AND I GOT THE PRESS ALL OVER ME.

14:32.664 --> 14:33.369
O KAY.

14:33.540 --> 14:35.622
LET'S GO SEE
YOUR BROTHER AND SISTER, THEN.

14:35.792 --> 14:36.827
THEY MIGHT BE ABLE
TO IDENTIFY YOU.

14:37.002 --> 14:37.912
THEY'RE STRANGERS TO ME,

14:38.086 --> 14:39.417
AND I PREFER
TO KEEP IT THAT WAY.

14:39.588 --> 14:42.375
I KNOW MY RIGHTS.
YOU CAN'T HOLD ME HERE.

14:42.549 --> 14:43.880
MAYBE NOT.

14:44.051 --> 14:45.291
BUT I CAN
TELL THOSE REPORTERS

14:45.469 --> 14:46.879
THAT YOU'RE
THE REAL WELLES VANBLARCOM,

14:47.054 --> 14:49.261
AND YOU'LL NEVER HAVE
ANOTHER MOMENT'S PRIVACY.

14:50.307 --> 14:53.765
OR WE COULD JUST TAKE A RIDE
AND TALK TO YOUR FAMILY.

14:55.187 --> 14:56.893
HYPOTHETICAL QUESTION.

14:57.105 --> 14:59.642
UM, SAY A CLIENT
THAT YOU REPRESENT
WAS RELEASED ON BAIL

14:59.858 --> 15:02.270
AND HE'S NOT EXACTLY WHERE
HE'S SUPPOSED TO BE.

15:03.362 --> 15:04.727
HENRY BOLTED,
DIDN'T HE?

15:04.905 --> 15:06.395
MAYBE.
YOU NEED TO FIND HIM

15:06.573 --> 15:08.609
BEFORE THE MONITORING COMPANY
REALIZES HE'S GONE.

15:08.825 --> 15:12.033
OTHERWISE, ALL THAT BAIL MONEY
IS OUT THE WINDOW, OKAY,

15:12.204 --> 15:13.990
AND HE'S IN JAIL EVERY DAY
UP UNTIL THE TRIAL.

15:14.164 --> 15:15.449
THAT -- THAT CAN'T HAPPEN

15:15.624 --> 15:17.580
BECAUSE HE BARELY MADE IT OUT
ALIVE LAST TIME.

15:19.002 --> 15:20.378
MAYBE I SHOULD CALL MY DAD.

15:20.587 --> 15:21.622
NO, NO, NO.
BAD IDEA.

15:21.797 --> 15:24.038
LISTEN, YOU'RE PROTECTED BY
ATTORNEY-CLIENT PRIVILEGE, OKAY,

15:24.216 --> 15:27.174
BUT ANYONE ELSE YOU TELL IS
REQUIRED BY LAW TO REVEAL IT,

15:27.386 --> 15:28.796
OR THEY COULD FACE
JAIL TIME.

15:29.304 --> 15:31.966
[SIGHS]
AND YOU REALLY SHOULDN'T EVEN BE
TELLING ME THIS

15:32.140 --> 15:35.132
UNLESS YOU'RE TRYING TO BRING ME
OFFICIALLY ONBOARD THE CASE.

15:35.352 --> 15:37.434
[CHUCKLES]
CAN'T AFFORD YOU.

15:37.646 --> 15:41.355
SO TELL ME, WHERE WOULD I FIND
HENRY IF HE WERE MISSING?

15:41.566 --> 15:43.352
HYPOTHETICALLY.
[CHUCKLES]

15:43.527 --> 15:45.233
[BIRDS CHIRPING, SQUAWKING]

15:51.785 --> 15:52.615
LOOK UP.

15:54.121 --> 15:55.361
HELLO.
I'M PENELOPE.

15:56.706 --> 15:58.287
I GUESS
I'M YOUR BROTHER.

15:58.458 --> 15:59.743
[SCOFFS]

16:00.460 --> 16:02.542
GIVEN
OUR FAMILY'S WEALTH,

16:02.712 --> 16:05.624
YOU CAN UNDERSTAND
WHY WE MIGHT BE SKEPTICAL.

16:06.425 --> 16:09.258
PERHAPS YOU COULD ANSWER
A FEW QUESTIONS, LIKE...

16:09.428 --> 16:10.713
WHERE WERE YOU BORN?

16:11.263 --> 16:12.673
IN A HOSPITAL,
I IMAGINE.

16:12.848 --> 16:14.679
CUT THAT OUT.

16:14.850 --> 16:17.262
WHAT WAS OUR MOM'S
FULL NAME?

16:17.477 --> 16:20.184
MOTHER?

16:20.397 --> 16:21.557
WHAT WAS MY NICKNAME?

16:22.274 --> 16:24.435
WELLES WAS THE ONLY ONE
WHO CALLED ME BY IT.

16:27.529 --> 16:29.190
HOW DARE YOU?

16:29.364 --> 16:30.604
YOU'RE NOT OUR BROTHER.

16:30.782 --> 16:33.649
FINE,
I'M NOT YOUR BROTHER.

16:33.827 --> 16:36.239
BUT I'M TELLING YOU THE GUY
IN THE MORGUE ISN'T, EITHER.

16:36.455 --> 16:38.571
[CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS]
HEY.

16:38.748 --> 16:40.124
[CELLPHONE CHIMES]
YOU'RE NOT TWEETING THAT.

16:40.333 --> 16:41.322
HEY, MAN.

16:45.380 --> 16:46.790
HEY!

16:46.965 --> 16:48.250
HEY,
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

16:48.425 --> 16:49.756
FAR FROM HERE.

16:49.926 --> 16:53.339
LOOK, ALL I WANTED WAS
TO DO RIGHT BY THAT POOR MAN.

16:53.513 --> 16:55.219
SO IF YOU'LL
JUST EXCUSE ME --
LOOK.

16:55.390 --> 16:57.756
WHETHER YOU'RE WELLES OR NOT,
I GOT A DEAD MAN IN THE MORGUE,

16:57.976 --> 16:58.761
AND SO FAR,
YOU'RE THE ONLY PERSON

16:58.977 --> 17:00.217
WHO KNOWS WHO HE IS.

17:00.437 --> 17:02.098
YOU'RE STAYING
TILL THIS THING IS SETTLED.

17:02.314 --> 17:03.804
WHERE? IN YOUR JAIL CELL?
ARE YOU ARRESTING ME?

17:04.024 --> 17:05.560
NO.

17:05.775 --> 17:08.517
NO, THERE'S, UH, TOO MANY
REPORTERS AT THE STATION.

17:08.695 --> 17:09.525
I KNOW A PLACE.

17:09.696 --> 17:10.856
IT'S NOT A HOTEL.

17:11.031 --> 17:12.646
THERE'S A COUCH
YOU COULD SLEEP ON.

17:14.242 --> 17:16.403
JUST NOTHING FANCY.

17:17.537 --> 17:19.573
[BIRD CRIES]

17:29.007 --> 17:31.464
OKAY,
THAT'S THE LAST ONE.

17:31.635 --> 17:32.966
[GRUNTS]

17:40.268 --> 17:42.429
LOOKS LIKE WE'RE LIVE.

17:42.646 --> 17:44.307
IT'S FANCY.

17:44.523 --> 17:46.764
I DIDN'T KNOW THE DEPARTMENT
HAD MONEY FOR GEAR LIKE THIS.

17:47.317 --> 17:49.353
THEY DON'T.
I BOUGHT THEM.

17:49.528 --> 17:50.483
[SIGHS]

17:50.654 --> 17:52.645
CAMERAS WILL SWITCH ON
IF ANYBODY COMES THROUGH HERE.

17:52.822 --> 17:54.073
[SNIFFS]

17:56.701 --> 17:58.237
BETTER FIND A CAMPSITE.

17:58.828 --> 18:00.204
I'M SORRY. A CAMPSITE?

18:00.372 --> 18:01.407
WE'RE GONNA
SLEEP OUT HERE?

18:01.915 --> 18:03.746
WHO SAID ANYTHING
ABOUT SLEEP?

18:03.917 --> 18:05.828
YOU GOT TO SLEEP
SOMETIME.

18:06.002 --> 18:07.117
WHAT ARE YOU DOING OUT HERE,
VIC?

18:07.295 --> 18:08.330
ISAID
I WAS FINE ON MY OWN.

18:08.505 --> 18:09.961
GO BACK.
TAKE MY TRUCK IF YOU WANT.

18:10.131 --> 18:11.587
I DON'T FEEL VERY COMFORTABLE
LEAVING YOU OUT HERE

18:11.758 --> 18:13.123
WHEN THERE'S A MURDERER
ON THE LOOSE.

18:13.301 --> 18:15.462
ESPECIALLY ONE THAT IS
SO HELL-BENT ON KILLING YOU.

18:16.388 --> 18:17.377
[SIGHS]

18:20.267 --> 18:22.178
THERE'S SOME EXTRA GEAR
IN THERE.

18:25.063 --> 18:26.223
DID THE TOX SCREEN SHOW

18:26.439 --> 18:27.599
WHAT KIND OF DRUG
HE OVERDOSED ON?

18:27.816 --> 18:29.056
IT WAS AN OPIATE
OF SOME KIND,

18:29.276 --> 18:31.437
BUT IT WAS TOO PURE
TO BE HEROIN, SO...

18:31.611 --> 18:32.771
[CELLPHONE BEEPING]

18:32.946 --> 18:34.436
...WE'RE RUNNING
SOME FURTHER TESTS.

18:34.614 --> 18:35.945
EXCUSE ME.

18:37.742 --> 18:39.448
] RATTLING ]

18:42.455 --> 18:45.947
WALT: SO, SOMEONE ELSE IS
CLAIMING TO BE YOU.

18:45.959 --> 18:47.950
I'M NOT SURE
IF I BELIEVE HIM,

18:48.128 --> 18:50.744
BUT SAYS YOU DIED
OF A DRUG OVERDOSE.

18:53.967 --> 18:56.208
[SIGHS]

18:57.679 --> 19:00.796
I DON'T SEE ANY TRACK MARKS
ON YOUR ARMS.

19:04.185 --> 19:06.927
HOW IS IT YOU CAN DISAPPEAR
FOR DECADES...

19:08.565 --> 19:11.682
AND SHOW UP
A FEW MILES FROM HOME

19:11.860 --> 19:13.725
RIGHT IN FRONT
OF MY STATION?

19:14.571 --> 19:16.277
WHERE WERE YOU BEFORE?

19:21.202 --> 19:23.864
BRYANT:
THOUGHT YOU'D BE WORKING
THE VANBLARCOM CASE.

19:24.497 --> 19:26.112
HOBNOBBING WITH MILLIONAIRES,

19:26.291 --> 19:28.156
NOT HANGING OUT
WITH THE HOMELESS.

19:28.543 --> 19:29.828
I'M DOING BOTH.

19:30.003 --> 19:32.164
HAS THE HIGH SCHOOL DONATED
ANY CLOTHES RECENTLY?

19:32.339 --> 19:34.170
YEAH, EVERY SUMMER, WE GET

19:34.341 --> 19:38.004
ALL THEIR UNSOLD SWEATSHIRTS
AND JERSEYS AND SOCKS.

19:38.178 --> 19:39.793
[CHUCKLES]
YOU NAME IT.

19:39.971 --> 19:41.427
THOUGHT THESE LOOKED
FAMILIAR.

19:41.598 --> 19:42.758
I WORE THE SAME COLORS

19:42.932 --> 19:44.183
WHEN I PLAYED FOOTBALL
FOR THE TEAM.

19:45.185 --> 19:46.550
B RYAN T.

19:48.146 --> 19:50.262
YOU REMEMBER GIVING THESE SOCKS
TO THIS MAN?

19:51.691 --> 19:53.101
YEAH, I REMEMBER HIM.

19:53.276 --> 19:56.313
HE CAME IN...
A FEW DAYS AGO WITH HIS FRIEND.

19:56.613 --> 19:58.353
WHICH FRIEND?

19:59.949 --> 20:02.281
YOU MIND IF I SIT,
SERGEANT?

20:10.293 --> 20:12.329
I WANT
TO ASK YOU SOME QUESTIONS

20:12.504 --> 20:14.961
ABOUT THE MAN YOU CAME
INTO THE SHELTER WITH.

20:15.715 --> 20:16.955
OH, YOU MEAN WELLES?

20:17.133 --> 20:18.464
YOU TWO ARE FRIENDS?

20:18.635 --> 20:20.375
SORT OF.

20:20.553 --> 20:22.635
MET HIM IN CLEVELAND
AWHILE BACK.

20:23.431 --> 20:26.764
HE'S A NICE GUY,
BUT WHEN YOU'RE ON THE STREET,

20:27.602 --> 20:28.717
IT'S REALLY EASY

20:28.895 --> 20:29.975
FOR A GUY LIKE HIM TO GET HURT,
YOU KNOW?

20:30.271 --> 20:32.978
SO STARTED LOOKING OUT
FOR HIM.

20:33.191 --> 20:34.852
YOU'RE A LONG WAY
FROM CLEVELAND.

20:35.026 --> 20:35.981
[CHUCKLES]

20:36.152 --> 20:37.358
WHAT BROUGHT YOU TWO
OUT HERE?

20:37.529 --> 20:40.111
WELLES JUST FOUND OUT
HE CAME INTO SOME MONEY.

20:40.281 --> 20:42.897
SAID HE'D CUT ME IN ON IT
IF I MADE THE TRIP WITH HIM.

20:44.035 --> 20:48.119
I SAID OKAY, BUT I DON'T KNOW
HOW MUCH I BELIEVE HIM.

20:48.957 --> 20:51.039
GUY'S KIND OF SCHIZO.

20:51.209 --> 20:53.325
HE EVER TELL YOU
ANYTHING ABOUT HIS FAMILY?

20:53.753 --> 20:54.663
NO.

20:54.838 --> 20:56.328
IASKED HIM
ABOUT THEM ONCE, BUT...

20:57.298 --> 20:58.424
HE GOT REAL DARK,

20:58.591 --> 21:00.923
STARTED SCREAMING SOME GIBBERISH
ABOUT HIS MOM.

21:01.970 --> 21:04.507
GOT THE FEELING SOMETHING BAD
HAPPENED BETWEEN THEM.

21:04.681 --> 21:07.468
WELL,
CONSIDERING HIS DRUG HABIT,

21:07.642 --> 21:09.553
FAMILY MIGHT'VE FOUND HIM
HARD TO HANDLE.

21:11.479 --> 21:13.344
UH,
WELLES NEVER DID DRUGS.

21:14.691 --> 21:16.773
HELL, THAT WAS
PART OF HIS PROBLEM.

21:16.943 --> 21:18.274
WOULDN'T EVEN TAKE
THE CRAZY MEDS

21:18.445 --> 21:19.810
THE, UH,
THE SHRINKS GAVE HIM.

21:21.239 --> 21:23.446
IS WELLES
IN SOME KIND OF TROUBLE?

21:23.616 --> 21:25.948
YOU'RE THE SECOND PERSON
TO ASK ME ABOUT HIM.

21:26.327 --> 21:27.453
WHO'S THE FIRST?

21:28.204 --> 21:31.367
SOME PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR
CAME AROUND TWO DAYS AGO,

21:31.541 --> 21:32.951
ASKING IF I'D SEEN WELLES.

21:33.918 --> 21:36.375
WAS A -- A BIG GUY.

21:37.255 --> 21:39.086
HAVE A BIRTHMARK
ON THE SIDE OF HIS FACE?

21:39.257 --> 21:40.463
YEAH.

21:40.633 --> 21:42.885
ANYWAY, I TOLD HIM, UH,
TOLD HIM I...

21:43.052 --> 21:45.759
I HADN'T SEEN WELLES
IN A FEW DAYS.

21:45.930 --> 21:49.297
WOKE UP TWO MORNINGS AGO
AND...WAS JUST GONE.

21:55.148 --> 21:58.640
WELLES IS...
DEAD, ISN'T HE?

21:59.986 --> 22:01.271
DRUG OVERDOSE.

22:02.405 --> 22:04.441
THEN SOMEBODY KILLED HIM.

22:05.742 --> 22:07.653
LOOKS THAT WAY.

22:12.415 --> 22:14.997
WHAT, YOU COME HERE TO GLOAT?
[CHUCKLES]

22:15.168 --> 22:17.124
I SEARCHED FOR WELLES VANBLARCOM
FOR YEARS.

22:17.295 --> 22:19.411
HE TURNS UP DEAD
ON YOUR DOORSTEP.

22:19.589 --> 22:21.045
WHEN DID YOU FIRST START LOOKING
FOR WELLES?

22:21.216 --> 22:22.296
EIGHT YEARS BACK.

22:22.467 --> 22:23.877
FAMILY HIRED ME

22:24.052 --> 22:25.838
ALONG WITH A BUNCH OF OTHER
AGENCIES AROUND THE COUNTRY.

22:26.429 --> 22:27.760
WE DIDN'T HAVE MUCH TO GO ON,
THOUGH.

22:27.931 --> 22:33.051
JUST THIS SKETCH SHOWING
WHAT HE WOULD'VE LOOKED LIKE

22:33.311 --> 22:34.596
30 YEARS LATER.

22:38.525 --> 22:40.356
I WAS GIVEN A DIFFERENT SKETCH
BY THE FAMILY.

22:40.527 --> 22:41.642
WELL,
IT'S NOT UNCOMMON

22:41.820 --> 22:43.060
TO HAVE
A FEW COMPOSITES DRAWN UP.

22:43.238 --> 22:44.648
THE FAMILY PROBABLY GAVE
DIFFERENT SKETCHES

22:44.823 --> 22:46.154
TO DIFFERENT INVESTIGATORS.

22:46.324 --> 22:48.690
I LOOKED FOR WELLES
FOR ABOUT A YEAR AND A HALF.

22:48.868 --> 22:50.074
TRACKED HIM
ALL THE WAY TO CLEVELAND,

22:50.245 --> 22:51.701
BUT THEN THE TRAIL
WENT COLD.

22:51.871 --> 22:55.705
THE FAMILY WAS ONLY PAYING ME
FOR TRAVEL AND FOOD,

22:55.875 --> 22:57.251
SO I DIDN'T MAKE
ENOUGH MONEY

22:57.418 --> 22:59.158
AND, YOU KNOW,
HAD TO CALL IT QUITS.

23:00.255 --> 23:01.461
AH.

23:01.631 --> 23:03.462
SO, WHY WERE YOU LOOKING FOR HIM
TWO DAYS AGO

23:03.675 --> 23:05.131
AT THE HOMELESS SHELTER?

23:05.552 --> 23:07.588
[CHUCKLES]
WELL, YOU KNOW HOW IT IS, WALT.

23:07.762 --> 23:10.504
IT'S HARD TO GIVE UP
ON THE CASES YOU DON'T SOLVE.

23:10.682 --> 23:13.674
I PURSUED WELLES FOR SO LONG,
AND THEN THE OTHER DAY,

23:13.893 --> 23:16.305
I SEE A GUY LOOKS
JUST LIKE MY SKETCH.

23:16.521 --> 23:18.603
I REALLY THOUGHT
I'D SEEN HIM.

23:18.815 --> 23:20.601
APPARENTLY, I DID.

23:22.110 --> 23:23.475
MIND IF I KEEP THIS?

23:23.653 --> 23:25.018
SURE.

23:25.196 --> 23:27.983
AND HEY, CONGRATS.

23:28.157 --> 23:29.488
I'M JUST GLAD TO SEE

23:29.659 --> 23:32.071
A LOCAL BOY GET
THAT BIG BONUS FROM THE FAMILY.

23:32.245 --> 23:34.156
WELL, SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT
DOESN'T GET REWARDS

23:34.330 --> 23:35.911
FOR DOING ITS JOB.

23:42.338 --> 23:44.750
[CELLPHONE RINGS]

23:47.302 --> 23:48.462
[SIGHS]

23:50.763 --> 23:51.969
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

23:52.140 --> 23:54.472
CADY, I AM SORRY
I DID NOT PICK UP EARLIER.

23:54.684 --> 23:55.639
DEAD BATTE RY.

23:55.810 --> 23:56.845
I JUST CHARGED IT
AND SAW YOU CALLED.

23:57.061 --> 23:58.847
37 TIMES.
WHERE ARE YOU?

23:59.063 --> 24:01.179
THERE WAS SOMETHING URGENT
I NEEDED TO TAKE CARE OF.

24:01.399 --> 24:02.900
NO, YOU CAN'T JUST TAKE OFF,
HENRY.

24:03.109 --> 24:04.690
WHEN SOMETHING COMES UP,
YOU ASK ME FOR HELP.

24:04.861 --> 24:05.816
YOU ASK MY DAD.

24:05.987 --> 24:07.978
CADY,
I AM TIRED OF EVERYBODY ELSE

24:08.156 --> 24:09.396
DOING THINGS FOR ME.

24:09.574 --> 24:11.565
I NEED TO TAKE MATTERS
INTO MY OWN HANDS.

24:11.743 --> 24:14.701
A GOOD MAN IS DEAD NOW
BECAUSE OF ME.

24:16.080 --> 24:17.786
I'M SORRY.

24:17.957 --> 24:20.539
I CAN'T IMAGINE
HOW HARD THAT MUST BE, BUT...

24:21.753 --> 24:22.868
THERE ARE A LOT OF PEOPLE HERE
THAT CARE ABOUT

24:23.046 --> 24:24.252
WHAT HAPPENS TO YOU.

24:25.423 --> 24:27.584
NONE OF US WANTS
TO SEE YOU BACK IN PRISON.

24:27.759 --> 24:30.341
IAM SORRY.
I WILL COME BACK NOW.

24:31.137 --> 24:32.001
SEE YOU SOON.

24:32.555 --> 24:33.465
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

24:34.891 --> 24:36.131
[CELLPHONE BEEPS]

24:37.894 --> 24:39.930
[SIGHS]
[KEYS JINGLE]

24:40.146 --> 24:41.761
[ENGINE TURNS OVER]

24:58.873 --> 25:01.034
YOU'VE REACHED
THE LONGMIRE RESIDENCE.

25:01.042 --> 25:02.578
SORRY WE'RE NOT HERE
TO TAKE YOUR CALL.

25:02.752 --> 25:04.413
PLEASE LEAVEA MESSAGE.
PICK UP, FERG.

25:04.587 --> 25:05.576
WE'LL BE HAPPY
TO CALL YOU BACK.

25:05.755 --> 25:06.961
PICK UP.
[TELEPHONE BEEPS]

25:07.131 --> 25:08.587
SORRY, SHERIFF.
I DIDN'T KNOW IT WAS YOU.

25:08.758 --> 25:10.123
THE CALLER I.D. SAID
"VANBLARCOM."

25:10.301 --> 25:13.213
I CONFISCATED A PHONE
FROM CARTER VANBLARCOM.

25:15.723 --> 25:17.679
[SCOFFS]
SNORmG.

25:17.850 --> 25:19.590
YOU FIND OUT ANYTHING NEW
ABOUT OUR VICTIM?

25:19.811 --> 25:21.017
WELL, I'M NOT SURE

25:21.229 --> 25:23.140
IF HE'S A DEAD HEIR
OR A DEAD IMPOSTER.

25:23.356 --> 25:24.937
EITHER WAY,
IT LOOKS LIKE HE WAS MURDERED.

25:25.149 --> 25:27.356
REALLY? BY WHO?

25:27.527 --> 25:29.643
I'M HAVING TROUBLE FINDING
ANYONE THAT KNEW HIM.

25:29.821 --> 25:31.561
HE HAD ONE BUDDY
AT THE HOMELESS SHELTER,

25:31.739 --> 25:33.195
AND THERE'S
A PRIVATE INVESTIGATOR

25:33.366 --> 25:34.776
WHO THINKS HE SAW HIM.

25:34.951 --> 25:36.441
OTHER THAN THAT,

25:36.619 --> 25:38.359
THE ONLY PERSON WHO SEEMS
TO HAVE MET THE VICTIM IS

25:38.538 --> 25:39.823
SLEEPING IN MY HOUSE.

25:46.129 --> 25:50.793
WHAT IF THIS JOHN GUY REALLY IS
WELLES VANBLARCOM?

25:50.967 --> 25:53.549
I MEAN, MAYBE THE DEAD GUY TRIED
TO BLACKMAIL HIM --

25:53.720 --> 25:56.928
YOU KNOW, THREATEN TO EXPOSE HIM
IF HE DIDN'T PAY UP.

25:57.098 --> 26:00.056
JOHN COULD'VE KILLED
OUR VICTIM

26:00.268 --> 26:02.554
AND THEN MADE UP THIS STORY
ABOUT SWAPPING IDENTITIES

26:02.770 --> 26:03.930
TO COVER HIS TRACKS.

26:04.147 --> 26:05.307
YOU'RE GETTING THE IDEA.

26:05.523 --> 26:07.514
YOU'RE BABYSITTING
A MURDER SUSPECT.

26:07.734 --> 26:09.144
KEEP YOUR EYES OPEN.

26:09.318 --> 26:11.570
ON IT.

26:11.738 --> 26:13.148
[TELEPHONE BEEPS]

26:20.913 --> 26:22.289
OH!

26:22.457 --> 26:23.321
[CHUCKLES]

26:24.125 --> 26:24.989
WHEW.

26:25.168 --> 26:27.033
GOOD MORNING.
UH, GOOD EVENING.

26:27.211 --> 26:28.121
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

26:35.344 --> 26:36.720
[SIGHS]
YOU'RE HERE LATE.

26:36.888 --> 26:39.846
YEP. YOU KNOW,
THE PHONES ARE BACK UP.

26:40.016 --> 26:42.507
I WANTED TO BE SURE I'VE GOT
ALL THESE MESSAGES WRITTEN DOWN

26:42.727 --> 26:43.762
BEFORE I WENT HOME.

26:43.978 --> 26:45.514
WHERE ARE ALL THE REPORTERS?

26:45.730 --> 26:47.686
WELL, SOME OF THEM ARE
PROBABLY DRINKING.

26:47.899 --> 26:48.934
[CHUCKLES]

26:49.150 --> 26:50.230
SOME ARE SLEEPING,

26:50.401 --> 26:52.016
AND SOME ARE POSTING
THEIR ARTICLES.

26:52.737 --> 26:54.944
RUBY,
IF YOU'D BEEN GIVEN THIS SKETCH,

26:55.531 --> 26:57.817
WOULD YOU HAVE KNOWN
TO FOLLOW OUR VICTIM?

27:00.036 --> 27:00.991
PROBABLY NOT.

27:01.162 --> 27:02.823
THEY DON'T LOOK
ALL THAT SIMILAR.

27:03.956 --> 27:04.866
WHAT ABOUT THIS ONE?

27:07.668 --> 27:09.659
THAT LOOKS
JUST LIKE HIM.

27:09.837 --> 27:11.043
O KAY.

27:11.214 --> 27:12.704
NOW THAT THE PHONES ARE
WORKING AGAIN,

27:12.882 --> 27:14.463
WOULD YOU MIND CALLING
THE PHONE COMPANY?

27:14.634 --> 27:16.340
HAVE THEM PULL THE RECORDS
ON FRED TAVISH.

27:16.511 --> 27:18.547
THAT'S THAT PRIVATE
INVESTIGATOR?
YEAH.

27:18.721 --> 27:21.383
UH, AND IN THE MORNING,
CALL DURANT FINANCIAL.

27:21.557 --> 27:22.967
I WANT TO TAKE A LOOK
AT HIS BANK RECORDS.

27:23.142 --> 27:24.598
O KAY, WA LT.

27:34.278 --> 27:35.438
HELLO, DEENA.

27:35.613 --> 27:38.150
OH, MY GOD.
I-I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

27:38.324 --> 27:39.154
COME IN.

27:39.325 --> 27:40.690
[DOOR CLOSES]

27:40.868 --> 27:42.699
HI, BABY.

27:42.870 --> 27:43.700
I TRIED CALLING YOU.

27:43.871 --> 27:45.122
WHEN I DIDN'T HEAR BACK,

27:45.289 --> 27:46.665
I THOUGHT MAYBE YOU WERE
ANGRY OR SOMETHING.

27:46.833 --> 27:50.792
DEENA, JUST --
JUST STOP FOR A SECOND.

27:51.838 --> 27:52.873
I DO NOT KNOW
IF YOU HEARD,

27:53.047 --> 27:55.379
BUT I SPENT A LITTLE TIME
IN JAIL.

27:55.550 --> 27:57.040
WHAT?

27:57.218 --> 27:58.549
HENRY, WHAT DID YOU --

27:58.719 --> 28:03.463
BEING THERE...GAVE ME
A LOT OF TIME TO THINK

28:03.641 --> 28:07.600
ABOUT WHAT IS REALLY
IMPORTANT TO ME.

28:07.812 --> 28:10.770
SO, DEENA...

28:11.357 --> 28:13.939
I HAVE A QUESTION
FOR YOU.

28:18.447 --> 28:20.278
OH.

28:21.159 --> 28:22.490
OH, MY GOD.

28:22.660 --> 28:23.695
DEENA...

28:23.870 --> 28:26.657
WHERE THE HELL IS
MY $40,000?

28:27.582 --> 28:28.947
YOU'RE JUST CRUEL.

28:29.125 --> 28:30.490
AND STEALING FROM ME
WAS NOT?!

28:30.751 --> 28:32.537
BETRAYING ME AGAIN?!
[SCREAMS]

28:32.712 --> 28:34.748
GET OUT! NOW!

28:34.922 --> 28:36.708
[CRIES]

28:38.718 --> 28:39.924
YOU WERE
THE ONLY OTHER PERSON

28:40.094 --> 28:41.334
WHO HAD THE COMBINATION
TO MY SAFE.

28:41.512 --> 28:42.797
OW!

28:44.473 --> 28:46.885
ARE YOU SLEEPING WITH THAT GUY
WHO JUST LEFT?

28:47.101 --> 28:49.717
[LAUGHS]

28:49.937 --> 28:53.100
DARIUS? OH, PLEASE.

28:54.775 --> 28:56.606
WHAT?
YOU WANT TO HURT ME?

28:56.777 --> 28:58.108
DO YOU WANT TO HIT ME?

28:59.113 --> 29:00.444
GO AHEAD!

29:00.615 --> 29:01.604
AAH!

29:03.159 --> 29:05.195
I WOULD NOT HIT YOU.

29:05.953 --> 29:07.489
BUT IF YOU DO NOT TELL ME
WHY YOU DID THIS TO ME,

29:07.663 --> 29:10.200
I WILL NOT BE THE ONLY ONE OF US
GOING TO PRISON.

29:13.628 --> 29:14.743
YOU'RE HURTING ME.

29:14.921 --> 29:16.377
[SCREAMS]

29:16.547 --> 29:17.377
SON OF A --

29:18.049 --> 29:19.334
DEENA: OH!

29:19.508 --> 29:21.635
I AM HURTING YOU?
YES!

29:21.802 --> 29:23.963
FORGET ABOUT THE FACT
THAT I CANNOT AFFORD A LAWYER

29:24.138 --> 29:26.003
OR THAT I CANNOT PAY
MY OWN BAIL!

29:26.182 --> 29:27.797
HOW DO YOU THINK I FEEL KNOWING
THAT THE WOMAN I LOVE

29:28.017 --> 29:29.257
STOLE FROM ME?!

29:29.477 --> 29:31.593
THAT WASN'T
PART OF THE DEAL!

29:35.858 --> 29:36.813
WHAT DEAL?

29:37.026 --> 29:39.813
I GOT --
I GOT INTO MONEY TROUBLE.

29:39.987 --> 29:42.854
THE KIND OF TROUBLE
THAT YOU LEAVE TOWN FOR.

29:45.910 --> 29:48.151
AND I...

29:48.913 --> 29:50.744
I MET DARIUS
AT A 9-BALL TOURNAMENT

29:50.915 --> 29:51.995
AT BACKSEAT BILLIARDS,

29:52.166 --> 29:55.374
AND HE OFFERED TO...
HELP GET ME RIGHT.

29:56.545 --> 29:58.160
IN EXCHANGE FOR A FAVOR?

29:58.339 --> 30:00.079
NOT THAT KIND OF FAVOR.

30:02.593 --> 30:05.505
HE JUST ASKED ME
TO GET IN CONTACT WITH YOU

30:05.680 --> 30:08.763
AND JUST KEEP TABS
ON THE BUSINESS AT THE RED PONY,

30:08.933 --> 30:10.013
AND THAT'S IT.

30:10.268 --> 30:12.054
AND HE ASKED YOU
TO STEAL FROM ME?

30:13.062 --> 30:15.144
BABY, HE DIDN'T ASK.

30:15.356 --> 30:17.187
[WHIMPERING]

30:20.778 --> 30:23.770
[VOICE BREAKING] I DIDN'T MEAN
TO HURT YOU, HENRY.

30:23.948 --> 30:25.358
[CRYING]

30:30.037 --> 30:32.744
HE DIDN'T GIVE ME
ANY CHOICE.

30:33.666 --> 30:35.497
THERE IS ALWAYS A CHOICE,
DEENA.

30:36.085 --> 30:38.497
IN THIS CASE,
WE BOTH JUST MADE THE WRONG ONE.

30:45.052 --> 30:46.553
WHERE'S MY DEPUTY?

30:46.721 --> 30:49.007
INSIDE.
HIDING ALL THE KNIVES.

30:49.557 --> 30:50.922
[CHUCKLES]

30:51.100 --> 30:52.431
WHAT DID YOU TELL HIM?

30:53.602 --> 30:55.217
THAT YOU'RE
A MURDER SUSPECT.

31:02.570 --> 31:04.731
THIS IS
A NICE LIFE YOU GOT.

31:05.823 --> 31:09.862
IF I HAD HAD THIS,
I WOULDN'T HAVE NEEDED TO LEAVE.

31:12.913 --> 31:14.744
YOU STILL DON'T
BELIEVE ME?

31:14.915 --> 31:17.531
YOU HAVEN'T DONE MUCH
TO CONVINCE ME, SO...

31:18.169 --> 31:21.502
I DON'T REALLY CARE WHETHER
YOU BELIEVE ME OR NOT, WALLY.

31:24.508 --> 31:26.123
THAT'S WHAT YOUR DAD
USED TO CALL YOU.

31:26.302 --> 31:29.169
WALLY. RIGHT?

31:29.347 --> 31:30.507
I REMEMBER.

31:30.681 --> 31:31.841
HE USED TO BRING YOU AROUND

31:32.016 --> 31:33.256
WHEN HE WAS WORKING
AT THE STABLES.

31:33.434 --> 31:34.344
YOU'RE LUCKY.

31:34.560 --> 31:35.345
YOUR DAD WORKED.

31:35.561 --> 31:36.721
HE WORKED HARD.

31:36.937 --> 31:38.188
YOU WORK.

31:38.397 --> 31:41.139
YOU APPRECIATE THE VALUE
OF THINGS IN YOUR MARROW.

31:41.359 --> 31:43.395
I NEEDED
TO GET AWAY FROM MY LIFE

31:43.569 --> 31:46.811
IF I WAS EVER GONNA KNOW
THAT FEELING.

31:48.699 --> 31:50.985
YOU NEVER FELT
THE URGE TO COME BACK?

31:51.160 --> 31:52.741
NOT EVEN
WHEN YOUR MOTHER WAS SICK?

31:56.123 --> 31:58.239
I TRIED CALLING ONCE.

31:58.417 --> 32:01.659
BUT BY THAT POINT...

32:01.837 --> 32:04.499
HER CANCER WAS
PRETTY ADVANCED.

32:04.673 --> 32:05.833
[SIGHS]

32:06.008 --> 32:08.875
AND SHE WAS SO DOPED UP
ON PAIN KILLERS,

32:09.053 --> 32:11.339
SHE DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
WHO I WAS.

32:12.640 --> 32:13.846
SO...

32:15.559 --> 32:17.766
I DECIDED
TO STAY OFF THE GRID.

32:19.188 --> 32:22.021
BUT YOU WERE NEVER REALLY
OFF THE GRID, WERE YOU?

32:22.233 --> 32:24.519
TOOK SOME MONEY
WITH YOU.

32:24.693 --> 32:26.558
WELL, I'M NOT STUPID.

32:26.737 --> 32:28.068
[CHUCKLES]

32:29.448 --> 32:31.313
YOU RECOGNIZE THIS MAN?

32:36.205 --> 32:39.697
LARGE AMOUNT OF MONEY WAS
DEPOSITED IN HIS ACCOUNT

32:39.875 --> 32:42.617
AROUND THE SAME TIME
HE STOPPED LOOKING FOR YOU.

32:43.421 --> 32:44.456
HE DIDN'T GET THAT MONEY

32:44.630 --> 32:45.836
FROM YOUR BROTHER
AND YOUR SISTER.

32:46.006 --> 32:48.133
DID YOU GIVE IT TO HIM?
HE FOUND ME IN CLEVELAND.

32:48.300 --> 32:51.713
I PAID HIM TO LEAVE ME ALONE
AND KEEP QUIET.

32:52.638 --> 32:54.799
HE DEFINITELY KNOWS
WHAT YOU LOOK LIKE?

32:54.974 --> 32:57.056
I'D SAY SO.

32:58.602 --> 33:00.217
RIGHT.

33:08.362 --> 33:10.193
I MADE BREAKFAST.

33:11.282 --> 33:12.567
EGGS.

33:13.576 --> 33:15.191
NO, THANKS.
I'LL PASS.

33:16.912 --> 33:18.527
AGAIN,
IF YOU WANT TO HEAD BACK...

33:20.166 --> 33:21.656
NO, IT'S FINE.

33:22.209 --> 33:24.040
I'LL WAIT
TILL WALT CAN GET HERE.

33:25.671 --> 33:27.662
YOU THINK
I CAN'T BE OUT HERE ON MY OWN?

33:29.592 --> 33:30.957
REALLY.

33:31.135 --> 33:33.126
I SAID IT'S OKAY.

33:34.096 --> 33:36.257
WHAT DO YOU THINK
I'M GONNA DO?

33:36.432 --> 33:37.467
[SIGHS]

33:37.641 --> 33:39.597
I DON'T KNOW, BRANCH.

33:40.019 --> 33:42.977
KIDNAP A GUY
AND FORCE HIM TO TAKE PEYOTE?

33:49.153 --> 33:51.064
TRAVIS TELL YOU THAT?

33:55.367 --> 33:56.948
SO, YOU'RE NOT GONNA
DENY IT?

33:58.829 --> 34:00.785
O KAY.

34:00.956 --> 34:03.698
MAYBE NOW YOU UNDERSTAND
WHY I AM NOT SO EXCITED

34:03.876 --> 34:05.707
TO LEAVE YOU
OUT HERE ALONE.

34:07.838 --> 34:09.874
YOU THINK
I'M LOSING IT.

34:10.633 --> 34:12.999
BUT YOU HAVE NO IDEA
WHAT IT'S LIKE TO KNOW THE TRUTH

34:13.177 --> 34:15.008
AND NOT HAVE
ANYONE BELIEVE YOU.

34:15.304 --> 34:16.054
[LAUGHS]

34:16.222 --> 34:18.213
THE ONLY WAY TO PROVE
THAT RIDGES WAS ALIVE

34:18.390 --> 34:20.676
AND THAT HE SHOT ME WAS
TO BREAK A COUPLE OF LAWS.

34:20.893 --> 34:22.884
TRAVIS AND I DIDN'T HURT
THAT GUY.

34:23.103 --> 34:25.480
WE JUST USED THE PEYOTE
HE ALREADY HAD ON HIM.

34:25.689 --> 34:27.520
AND LET'S NOT FORGET
I WAS RIGHT ABOUT RIDGES.

34:27.733 --> 34:28.518
[SCOFFS]

34:28.734 --> 34:29.723
OH, COME ON!

34:30.152 --> 34:31.688
WE BOTH WORK FOR A MAN

34:31.904 --> 34:33.189
WHO DOESN'T STOP
UNTIL HE HAS ANSWERS.

34:33.405 --> 34:35.236
DON'T YOU COMPARE YOURSELF
TO WALT!

34:35.824 --> 34:36.779
RIGHT.

34:36.951 --> 34:39.488
I FORGOT YOU TWO HAVE
A SPECIAL RELATIONSHIP.

34:41.205 --> 34:42.490
LISTEN.

34:42.665 --> 34:46.624
I'D UNDERSTAND IF YOU FELT
YOU HAD TO TELL WALT.

34:46.794 --> 34:49.331
BUT THIS ISN'T ABOUT ME TRYING
TO SAVE MY JOB.

34:49.547 --> 34:52.004
THIS IS ABOUT ME TRYING TO FIND
THE MAN WHO SHOT ME,

34:52.216 --> 34:54.172
WHO SCALPED
AND MURDERED HECTOR,

34:54.343 --> 34:57.585
AND, FOR ALL WE KNOW,
MAY BE COMING BACK FOR ME.

34:58.597 --> 35:00.713
SO YOU DO
WHAT YOU GOT TO DO.

35:00.891 --> 35:05.351
BUT I'LL TELL YOU NOW --
MY CONSCIENCE IS CLEAR.

35:11.026 --> 35:12.482
I GOT TO PEE.

35:18.492 --> 35:20.198
[P.A. DINGS]

35:20.369 --> 35:23.486
WALT LONGMIRE
TO SEE PENNY AND GRAHAM.

35:26.375 --> 35:28.457
[SIGHS]

35:33.340 --> 35:35.126
[GATE BUZZES]

35:39.138 --> 35:41.299
THAT'S GOOD.

35:48.105 --> 35:50.391
BUT THE MAN I BROUGHT IN EARLIER
IS, UH, REFUSING

35:50.608 --> 35:51.723
TO SUBMIT TO THE TESTS.

35:51.942 --> 35:53.443
CAN'T YOU MAKE HIM?

35:53.611 --> 35:55.397
I CAN'T FORCE A MAN TO INHERIT
MONEY HE DOESN'T WANT.

35:55.571 --> 35:56.560
[DOOR CLOSES]

35:56.739 --> 35:59.230
A MR. TAVISH IS HERE
TO SEE YOU.

35:59.408 --> 36:01.740
FRED?
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

36:01.910 --> 36:03.571
I GOT YOUR TEXT.

36:03.746 --> 36:05.202
"FRED, IT'S PENNY.
COME RIGHT OVER."

36:06.040 --> 36:09.578
ACTUALLY, UH...
THAT WAS ME.

36:10.961 --> 36:12.246
THESE THINGS ARE
PRETTY HANDY.

36:12.796 --> 36:13.626
[CHUCKLES]

36:13.797 --> 36:14.877
SO, UH...

36:16.133 --> 36:17.714
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU SAW FRED?

36:18.260 --> 36:20.637
SIX, SEVEN YEARS AGO,
I GUESS.

36:20.888 --> 36:21.638
OH.

36:22.222 --> 36:23.348
WELL,
YOU RESPOND PRETTY FAST

36:23.515 --> 36:25.426
TO PEOPLE
YOU'RE SO OUT OF TOUCH WITH.

36:25.601 --> 36:27.011
WELL,
THEY WERE GOOD CLIENTS.

36:27.227 --> 36:28.478
UH-HUH.

36:28.687 --> 36:30.268
SO, YOU DIDN'T THINK
YOU'D BEEN CALLED HERE

36:30.481 --> 36:31.641
TO RECEIVE A BONUS?

36:32.441 --> 36:34.397
EVEN THOUGH YOU ALREADY GOT ONE
YEARS AGO

36:34.610 --> 36:36.475
WHEN YOU ACTUALLY FOUND
WELLES

36:36.654 --> 36:39.066
AND HE PAID YOU
NOT TO SAY ANYTHING.

36:39.531 --> 36:40.566
YOU FOUND WELLES?

36:41.909 --> 36:44.901
SEE, HERE'S WHAT
I DON'T UNDERSTAND, FRED.

36:45.079 --> 36:46.694
YOU KNEW
WHAT THEIR BROTHER LOOKED LIKE,

36:46.872 --> 36:49.284
SO WHY WERE YOU HUNTING DOWN
THIS GUY?

36:50.626 --> 36:51.615
NOW, LOOK, I --

36:51.794 --> 36:53.204
HE DOESN'T EVEN LOOK
ANYTHING LIKE

36:53.379 --> 36:55.210
THE SKETCH YOU WERE GIVEN
EIGHT YEARS AGO.

36:57.925 --> 37:00.257
UNLESS YOU WERE WORKING
OFF THIS SKETCH.

37:01.804 --> 37:03.010
HOW WOULD I HAVE
GOTTEN THAT?

37:04.098 --> 37:05.338
FROM PENNY AND GRAHAM.

37:06.266 --> 37:07.255
WELL, THEY JUST TOLD YOU

37:07.518 --> 37:08.883
I HAVEN'T TALKED TO THEM
IN SEVEN YEARS.

37:09.103 --> 37:10.593
ACCORDING
TO YOUR PHONE RECORDS,

37:10.813 --> 37:12.269
YOU'VE HAD FOUR CALLS
FROM THIS HOUSE

37:12.481 --> 37:13.596
IN THE PAST WEEK.

37:16.193 --> 37:19.026
YOUR DRAWING SKILLS HAVE
REALLY GOTTEN BETTER, PENNY.

37:19.196 --> 37:21.061
I DIDN'T KNOW
IT WAS YOUR WORK AT FIRST.

37:21.240 --> 37:23.026
I THOUGHT
IT LOOKED LIKE A POLICE SKETCH.

37:23.659 --> 37:25.570
BUT THE PERSPECTIVE WAS
WRONG.

37:25.744 --> 37:27.405
ALMOST LOOKED LIKE A --

37:27.579 --> 37:29.319
LIKE AN IMAGE
FROM A SECURITY CAMERA.

37:29.498 --> 37:31.489
LIKE THE ONE
AT YOUR FRONT GATE.

37:31.667 --> 37:32.907
[P.A. DINGS]

37:33.085 --> 37:34.791
THE VICTIM CAME TO THIS HOUSE,
DIDN'T HE?

37:35.462 --> 37:37.418
HIS IMAGE WAS CAUGHT
ON THE CAMERA.

37:37.589 --> 37:40.456
YOU DREW IT
AND GAVE IT TO FRED TAVISH.

37:42.136 --> 37:44.172
PENNY:
YES, ALL -- ALL RIGHT.

37:44.346 --> 37:47.930
I GAVE FRED THE SKETCH,
BUT THAT MAN WAS HARASSING US,

37:48.142 --> 37:50.758
AND I HIRED FRED TO FIND HIM
AND MAKE HIM STOP.

37:51.186 --> 37:52.562
WHY DIDN'T YOU CALL ME?

37:53.647 --> 37:55.308
IS THAT
WHAT PEOPLE DO?

37:55.524 --> 37:57.936
WELL, PEOPLE THAT DON'T HAVE
SOMETHING TO HIDE.

37:58.110 --> 38:00.317
[CHUCKLES]
I DON'T HAVE ANYTHING TO --

38:00.487 --> 38:02.068
WHY WOULD I HAVE
SOMETHING TO HIDE?

38:02.698 --> 38:03.778
FRED NEVER FOUND
THE MAN.

38:03.949 --> 38:06.611
YOU WERE THE ONE
WHO FOUND HIM DEAD.

38:06.785 --> 38:08.400
AND YOU IDENTIFIED HIM
AS YOUR BROTHER,

38:08.579 --> 38:10.444
EVEN THOUGH YOU KNEW
HE WAS AN IMPOSTER.

38:10.831 --> 38:12.492
EVER SINCE
OUR MOTHER PASSED,

38:12.666 --> 38:15.248
WE'VE BEEN THE VICTIMS
OF CON ARTISTS.

38:15.502 --> 38:17.117
I JUST --
IF I SAID HE WAS MY BROTHER,

38:17.296 --> 38:18.581
IT WOULD PUT AN END TO IT.

38:18.756 --> 38:20.292
I JUST WANTED IT ALL
OVER WITH.

38:20.883 --> 38:23.249
HOW BADLY DID YOU WANT IT
TO BE OVER?

38:23.427 --> 38:27.170
ENOUGH TO HIRE FRED
TO FIND A MAN AND KILL HIM?

38:27.973 --> 38:32.012
YOU TOLD US
IT WAS AN OVERDOSE.

38:32.227 --> 38:35.310
SO, HOW DOES
AN ACCIDENTAL OVERDOSE

38:35.522 --> 38:37.262
OF A HOMELESS ADDICT BECOME
MURDER?

38:37.483 --> 38:40.691
IT'S MURDER WHEN THE VICTIM
DOESN'T TAKE DRUGS.

38:40.861 --> 38:43.398
WHEN THE DRUGS IN THE SYSTEM ARE
THE SAME GIVEN

38:43.572 --> 38:45.813
TO CANCER PATIENTS IN PAIN

38:45.991 --> 38:47.606
AND THE DRUG IS AN OPIATE,

38:47.785 --> 38:50.902
IT CAN BE CONFUSED WITH HEROIN
IN A TOX SCREEN.

38:51.663 --> 38:53.449
MY WIFE USED IT
DURING HER CANCER TREATMENT.

38:53.624 --> 38:57.537
I ASSUME YOUR MOTHER USED IT
DURING HERS.

38:57.711 --> 38:59.292
AND SEEING AS HOW THIS, UH,

38:59.463 --> 39:01.829
THIS PLACE IS PRESERVED
LIKE A SHRINE,

39:02.007 --> 39:03.793
I'LL BET I CAN FIND IT
IN HER MEDICINE CABINETS

39:03.967 --> 39:05.343
WHEN I SEARCH THE HOUSE.

39:05.594 --> 39:06.379
[SCOFFS]

39:06.553 --> 39:08.418
DID YOU GIVE THOSE DRUGS TO FRED
TO KILL THAT MAN?

39:08.597 --> 39:10.462
I DIDN'T KILL ANYBODY!
FRED, JUST SIT DOWN.

39:10.641 --> 39:12.051
FRED, SIT DOWN.
PENNY CALLED ME.

39:12.226 --> 39:14.262
SHE SAID SOME BUM CAME
TO THEIR DOOR,

39:14.478 --> 39:15.593
CLAIMING HE WAS WELLES.

39:15.813 --> 39:17.519
SHE KICKED HIM TO THE CURB,

39:17.731 --> 39:19.642
BUT THEN SHE REALIZED
THAT SHE COULD USE THAT GUY

39:19.858 --> 39:21.394
TO GET HER HANDS
ON WELLES' MONEY.

39:21.568 --> 39:24.651
SO SHE DECIDED TO OFFER
THE HOMELESS MAN A MILLION BUCKS

39:24.822 --> 39:27.154
TO SIGN PAPERWORK SAYING
THAT HE WAS WELLES

39:27.324 --> 39:29.235
AND FORFEITING
HIS INHERITANCE.

39:29.409 --> 39:31.866
ONLY PROBLEM WAS
HE WOULDN'T GO FOR IT.

39:32.037 --> 39:33.698
THE GUY WAS CONVINCED
HE REALLY WAS WELLES,

39:33.872 --> 39:35.373
AND HE WANTED
ALL THE MONEY.

39:35.624 --> 39:37.455
I THOUGHT THAT WAS THAT,

39:37.626 --> 39:38.741
AND THEN SHE CAME BACK IN

39:38.919 --> 39:40.659
AND JAMMED THE GUY
WITH A NEEDLE.

39:40.838 --> 39:42.578
PENNY TOLD ME I COULD
STILL GET PAID

39:42.756 --> 39:44.587
IF I WOULD DUMP THE BODY
WHERE IT COULD BE FOUND.

39:44.758 --> 39:46.294
THAT WAY,
SHE COULD I.D. HIM LATER

39:46.468 --> 39:48.754
AND GET WELLES' MONEY.

39:52.099 --> 39:54.090
YOU THINK
IT WAS ABOUT THE MONEY?

39:56.061 --> 39:58.473
IT WAS NEVER
ABOUT THE MONEY.

39:58.689 --> 40:00.225
OUR BROTHER JUST TOOK OFF.

40:00.983 --> 40:02.814
YOUR BROTHER JUST WANTED TO BE
LEFT ALONE.

40:04.236 --> 40:06.067
NO, HE ABANDONED US.

40:07.406 --> 40:12.651
HE TURNED HIS BACK
ON OUR FAMILY, ON EVERYTHING.

40:12.828 --> 40:14.693
HE KNEW
HOW CRUEL OUR MOTHER WAS,

40:14.872 --> 40:16.533
AND HE LEFT ME
TO TAKE CARE OF HER.

40:18.250 --> 40:19.660
I NURSED HER.

40:20.669 --> 40:22.205
I GAVE HER HER MEDICATIONS.

40:22.379 --> 40:24.665
I TOOK CARE
OF HER DAMN BIRDS.

40:26.633 --> 40:30.171
I GAVE UP MY LIFE
FOR THAT WOMAN.

40:31.305 --> 40:32.545
[VOICE BREAKING]
AND HE GOT ALL HER AFFECTION.

40:32.723 --> 40:33.758
[SNIFFLES]

40:40.981 --> 40:42.471
JUST WASN'T FAIR.

40:44.818 --> 40:46.149
IT'S NOT FAIR
TO TAKE YOUR REVENGE

40:46.320 --> 40:48.106
ON AN INNOCENT MAN,
EITHER.

40:49.281 --> 40:50.862
PENNY.

41:02.753 --> 41:04.334
[HANDCUFFS CLICK]

41:07.090 --> 41:09.672
THANK YOU.
I APPRECIATE YOUR UNDERSTANDING.

41:09.843 --> 41:11.879
NO PROBLEM.
TAKE CARE OF YOURSELF.

41:20.771 --> 41:22.978
YOU'RE LUCKY I WAS HERE
TO STALL HIM FOR HALF AN HOUR.

41:23.190 --> 41:24.350
I AM ALSO LUCKY
THAT I COULD FIT

41:24.566 --> 41:25.772
THROUGH THE WINDOW
IN MY OFFICE.

41:25.984 --> 41:27.019
IT IS MORE NARROW
THAN I RECALL.

41:27.527 --> 41:28.516
WHERE WERE YOU?

41:29.029 --> 41:32.362
YOU SAID THAT YOU WERE GONNA BE
RIGHT BACK.

41:35.410 --> 41:37.275
I NEED
TO TALK TO YOUR FATHER.

41:43.210 --> 41:45.326
I HAVE GOOD NEWS.

41:45.504 --> 41:46.789
I BROKE UP WITH DEENA.

41:47.464 --> 41:48.624
DEENA CAME HERE?

41:50.050 --> 41:52.541
I ALSO MANAGED TO GET A PICTURE
OF MALACHI'S GUY.

41:56.932 --> 41:59.924
HENRY, THIS PICTURE WASN'T TAKEN
AT THE RED PONY.

42:00.143 --> 42:01.007
NO, IT WAS NOT.

42:01.228 --> 42:02.559
HEY!

42:02.771 --> 42:04.181
I'M YOUR LAWYER,

42:04.398 --> 42:06.889
SO YOU DON'T GET TO HAVE
PRIVATE CONVERSATIONS ANYMORE.

42:07.109 --> 42:08.565
WHAT'S GOING ON?

42:10.404 --> 42:12.565
HIS NAME IS DARIUS.
HE WORKS FOR MALACHI.

42:12.739 --> 42:14.604
I FOUND OUT
HE BLACKMAILED MY EX-GIRLFRIEND

42:14.783 --> 42:16.023
INTO STEALING MY MONEY.

42:16.201 --> 42:17.566
HE APPROACHED HER
A COUPLE OF MONTHS AGO

42:17.744 --> 42:18.995
AT BACKSEAT BILLIARDS.

42:19.871 --> 42:21.372
BACKSEAT BILLIARDS?

42:21.540 --> 42:22.620
THAT'S IN DENVER.

42:22.791 --> 42:24.406
YES.

42:25.210 --> 42:28.327
MALACHI STRAND HAS PEOPLE
WORKING FOR HIM IN DENVER.

42:31.550 --> 42:34.257
IS THIS THE GUY
THAT HAD MOM KILLED?
